{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ff8eb091-b457-447f-96c4-ab127eff363e","content":"Here's the report of static dependencies in your **source files** (excluding `obj/` and `bin/`):\n\n---\n\n### Static Dependencies — `Services/DataService.cs`\n\n| Static Call | Why It Hurts Testability |\n|---|---|\n| `DateTime.UtcNow` | Non-deterministic; tests can't control time |\n| `Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable()` | Couples logic to process environment |\n| `Path.Combine()` | Low risk (pure function), but wrapping it with the others keeps path logic injectable |\n| `File.WriteAllText()` | Side effect — writes to disk |\n| `File.ReadAllText()` | Side effect — reads from disk |\n| `Directory.GetFiles()` | Side effect — queries file system |\n| `Console.WriteLine()` | Side effect — writes to stdout |\n\n### `Program.cs`\n\n| Static Call | Notes |\n|---|---|\n| `Console.WriteLine()` | Entry point — typically left as-is |\n\n---\n\n### Recommended Wrapping Strategy\n\n1. **`IDateTimeProvider`** — abstract `DateTime.UtcNow`\n2. **`IFileSystem`** (or use `System.IO.Abstractions`) — abstract `File.*`, `Directory.*`, `Path.*`\n3. **`IEnvironment`** — abstract `Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable`\n4. **`IConsole` / `ILogger`** — abstract `Console.WriteLine`\n\nInject these interfaces into `DataService` via constructor injection, making the class fully unit-testable without touching the real filesystem, clock, or environment.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"87b60dbd-75dc-4aed-880a-406b1290924a","outputTokens":379,"requestId":"BD02:AA16B:1DCB4ED:218B499:6A07C70D"},"id":"bea5e33e-ead9-4227-b1cd-5d26b441eef4","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:23:34.749Z","parentId":"7a9bc344-4ab5-4605-bc89-99eac22a516e"}
